    "image_prompt": "Editorial tech thumbnail, 16:9. Incorporate the brand logo fetched from https://logo.clearbit.com/invideo.io as the clean focal element over a soft amber-to-cream gradient (Notion + Apple aesthetic). A person sitting at a laptop with a glowing text prompt box on screen, transforming into a colorful video timeline with thumbnails, a microphone icon, and subtitle bars floating around the workspace. Glassmorphism cards, soft volumetric light, generous negative space for a title, no embedded text, no watermark. --ar 16:9 --style raw",
    "faq_items": [
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How many videos can I create with the Plus plan?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The Plus plan ($17/month) gives you 75 credits monthly. Depending on the generation mode, that translates to roughly 300 shorter videos or 600 lightweight outputs. For most creators publishing a few times a week, this is more than enough to stay productive without worrying about limits.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Do I need video editing experience to use InVideo AI?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Not at all. InVideo AI was designed for people with zero editing experience. You type a text prompt describing what you want, and the AI generates the script, selects footage, adds voiceover, subtitles, and transitions automatically. The customization tools are drag-and-drop simple — closer to Canva than Adobe Premiere.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can I use InVideo AI videos for commercial purposes?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes. Every paid plan includes unlimited exports without watermarks, and you own the output. This means you can publish videos on YouTube, run them as ads on Meta or Google, use them in client presentations, or sell them as part of a service — no additional licensing required. The iStock assets included in your plan also come with commercial usage rights.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
